humanMachineDialogue.text: According to the report, 'METASTATIC CARCINOMA IS PRESENT IN 5 OF 18 AXILLARY LYMPH NODES.' This corresponds to N1 stage as per Rule 12: N1 indicates metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes (No/Total).

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report mentions the identification of 18 axillary lymph nodes, with 5 of them being positive for metastatic carcinoma. This corresponds to a pathologic N stage of N1 (pN1). The specific number of positive lymph nodes is not provided for N1mi, N1a, or N1b, so we cannot make a more specific N1 subclassification. The presence of metastatic carcinoma in any number of axillary lymph nodes is classified as N1.
